  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This internal processing ensures the system's operational closure while remaining open to external stimuli, which it observes and integrates based on its operational logic.",
    "The scientific system is a functional system of modern functionally differentiated society, distinguishing between true and false information and meaning through internally differentiated programs of theory and methodology (Luhmann 1995; Roth 2024).",
    "This distinction-based understanding emphasizes that the parts (individual researchers, technological tools, etc.)",
    "are not merely components of a larger whole but are integrated into the system's operations through complex interactions and mutual influences.",
    "The scientific system, thus, maintains its identity and functionality by continuously regenerating its elements and adapting to external irritations, demonstrating the dynamic relationship between parts and the whole within a system."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The scientific system is a functional system of modern functionally differentiated society, distinguishing between true and false information and meaning through internally differentiated programs of theory and methodology (Luhmann 1995; Roth 2024)."
  ]
}